Path System Overview
Core design rule:
Unlocking one piece of equipment can trigger a chain reaction that activates special interactions with another piece of equipment.

Multi-element synergy rule:
Example: Water + Lightning creates chained area damage that links enemies within shock range.

Baseline implementation status:
Ballistic Path: initial prototype (Pierce, Ricochet, Shrapnel).
Turret Path: baseline variants (Auto, Stationary).
Shield Path: working baseline (Carapace, Bone Plating, Shield AOE).
Economy Path: baseline systems (Coin, Coupon, Reroll).
Status Path: baseline systems (Buff, Debuff, Status).
Status Path runtime rule: leave a trace while moving; enemies in the area receive a status effect.
Status Path cleanup rule: the effect expires after the player leaves the area for a short time, or on death, restart, or level clear.
Summoner Path: baseline systems (Pet, Minion, Summoner).
Summoner Path baseline behavior: summons follow the player, attack enemies, respawn after death, level with the player, and have unique active and passive abilities.
Lucky Path: baseline systems (Lucky, Risk, Chance).

Path Archetype Summary
Ballistic Path
Fantasy: high projectile mastery and wave-clearing combos.
Key scaling stats: projectile count, pierce count, ricochet count, projectile speed.
Signature mechanics: hit chaining, wall-assisted bounces, kill-triggered shrapnel bursts.
Weakness: underperforms when maps have low enemy density or poor bounce angles.

Turret Path
Fantasy: controlled zone defense with independent damage sources.
Key scaling stats: turret count, duration, fire rate, lock-on range.
Signature mechanics: auto turret tracking and stationary burst zones.
Weakness: vulnerable to fast reposition encounters and forced-movement bosses.

Shield Path
Fantasy: survive pressure and convert defense into controlled retaliation.
Key scaling stats: shield capacity, recharge, shield-on-hit effects, break effects.
Signature mechanics: one-time protection, plating stacks, shield pulse damage.
Weakness: lower ceiling if the player avoids all damage and never triggers shield reactions.

Economy Path
Fantasy: leverage resources to snowball through smarter resource decisions instead of raw combat stats.
Key scaling stats: coin gain multiplier, shop discount, reroll efficiency, protected coins.
Signature mechanics: better shop control, safer greed choices, compound value over time.
Weakness: weak immediate combat power if the path is over-invested too early.

Status Path
Fantasy: control tempo through damage-over-time and debuff layers.
Key scaling stats: status duration, tick damage, stack cap, application chance.
Signature mechanics: trail zones, persistent debuffs, area denial through status fields.
Weakness: slower burst against urgent threats without setup time.

Summoner Path
Fantasy: indirect power through companions and team-based combat flow.
Key scaling stats: summon count, summon damage ratio, summon uptime, respawn speed.
Signature mechanics: autonomous minions, command-based focus fire, summon-specific synergies.
Weakness: AI and pathing downtime reduce real DPS in cluttered arenas.

Lucky Path
Fantasy: high-variance run shaping through risk and reward decisions.
Key scaling stats: trigger chance, jackpot multiplier, fail penalty, reroll interaction.
Signature mechanics: chance-based spikes, gamble props, and a high ceiling with an unstable floor.
Weakness: inconsistent runs without protection mechanics.

Cross-Path Design Rules
Every major path should have at least 2 bridge props that connect it to two other paths.
No single path should solve both elite waves and bosses without trade-offs.
Utility paths (Economy and Status) should scale into strength over time, not deliver full value instantly.
High-variance paths must include at least one stabilizer option for consistency.
Economy Path and Control Path should remain universal side branches that can hybridize with any primary archetype.
Status Path, Summoner Path, and Lucky Path should expand gradually only after their core loops are stable.

Path Tuning Targets
Global run brackets:
Early: waves 1-5
Mid: waves 6-12
Late: waves 13+

Enemy scaling targets:
enemy_hp_multiplier = 1.00 / 1.85 / 3.10 (early, mid, late)
enemy_damage_multiplier = 1.00 / 1.35 / 1.80
elite_spawn_ratio = 8% / 16% / 24%

Path activation thresholds:
A path is online when the player owns >= 2 tagged props from that path.
A path is fully online when the player owns >= 4 tagged props from that path.

Ballistic Path numeric targets:
effective_hit_count = 1 + pierce_count + (ricochet_count * 0.60)
shrapnel_proc_chance_cap = 55%
projectile_count_soft_cap = +4 (extra projectiles after cap deal 50% damage)
target DPS gain from online to fully online = +35% to +55%

Turret Path numeric targets:
max_active_turrets = 1 / 2 / 3 (by progression tier)
turret_damage_ratio_vs_player = 0.45 / 0.55 / 0.65
turret_duration = 8s base, +1.5s per level, capped at 16s
retarget_interval = 0.25s minimum to avoid visual jitter

Shield Path numeric targets:
shield_hp_gain_per_pick = +12 / +18 / +25
shield_recharge_delay = 5.0s base, minimum 2.5s
shield_break_explosion_ratio = 0.35 * player_bullet_base
max_total_shield_from_props = 220 before temporary buffs

Economy Path numeric targets:
coin_gain_bonus_per_level = +8% (cap +56%)
shop_discount_per_level = 4% (cap 20%)
reroll_cost_growth = +1 coin per reroll, capped at 12
safety rule: if DPS is below threshold, offer one combat-biased shop slot

Status Path numeric targets:
base_status_apply_chance = 18% / 24% / 30%
status_duration_bonus_per_level = +0.4s (cap +2.4s)
dot_tick_interval = 0.5s fixed for readability
max_parallel_damage_statuses_on_single_target = 3

Summoner Path numeric targets:
summon_count_base = 1, hard_cap = 3
summon_damage_ratio = 0.35 / 0.45 / 0.55 (early, mid, late)
summon_hp_ratio_vs_player = 0.60 / 0.80 / 1.00
summon_crit_inherit = min(player_crit * 0.40, 35%)
summon_fire_rate_inherit = min(player_fire_rate_bonus * 0.50, +80%)
summon_respawn_time = 6.0s base, floor 2.5s
boss_damage_penalty_default = -25% unless overridden by summon-specialized props

Lucky Path numeric targets:
high_roll_trigger_chance = 12% base, cap 35%
fail_penalty_limit = no more than -20% effective run DPS at full stack
expected_value_rule = over 10 encounters, Lucky Path should produce +5% to +12% average value
variance rule = standard deviation should stay below one shop purchase equivalent per wave

Summoner Command and AI Specification
Command inputs:
Focus command cooldown = 8s, duration = 4s, bonus damage during focus = +20%
Regroup command cooldown = 6s, summons orbit the player for 2.5s
Hold Position command cooldown = 10s, hold radius = 1.5 tiles, duration = 5s

AI movement tuning:
follow_distance = 1.2 tiles
leash_break_distance = 5.0 tiles
teleport_back_delay_when_leash_broken = 1.0s
avoid_overlap_separation_radius = 0.55 tiles

AI target scoring:
score = (threat_weight * enemy_threat) + (distance_weight / distance) + mark_bonus
recommended weights: threat_weight = 0.6, distance_weight = 0.3, mark_bonus = 0.4
forced retarget if the current target is unreachable for > 0.75s

Summoner progression breakpoints:
Level 1-2: baseline summon only, no branch passive
Level 3: choose branch (Swarm Commander, Arcane Familiar, Warden Totem)
Level 6: unlock branch active-skill modifier
Level 9: unlock branch capstone passive
Level 10+: horizontal growth only (utility and consistency), no major raw DPS spike

Summoner Path Build Draft
Core identity:
Lower direct burst from the player; higher map control and sustained team DPS through summons.

Core rules:
Base max summons = 1. Hard cap = 3 (only through rare props or upgrades).
Summon base damage scales from player bullet_base at a reduced ratio.
Suggested damage ratio by tier = 35% / 45% / 55% (early, mid, late unlock tiers).
Summon crit chance inherits 40% of player crit chance, capped at 35%.
Summon attack speed inherits 50% of player fire-rate bonuses, with a hard cap.
Respawn delay after summon death = 6.0s base, reducible to a 2.5s minimum.

AI behavior package:
Default: follow the player at medium leash distance.
In combat: prioritize marked and high-threat enemies first.
Safety: teleport back after a short timeout if too far from the player.
Command skill: Focus mode forces all summons to attack one target for 4s.

Build branches:
Swarm Commander: more summon count, lower per-unit damage, strong with on-hit effects.
Arcane Familiar: fewer summons, higher single-target DPS, better boss pressure.
Warden Totem: defensive summon that grants shield pulses and slow zones.

Recommended synergy tags:
Summon + Status: summons apply bleed, burn, or slow stacks.
Summon + Economy: summon kills can drop bonus coin shards.
Summon + Shield: while shielded, summons gain damage reduction and taunt chance.
Summon + AoE: summon kills create a mini-explosion or shrapnel burst.

Balance constraints:
Summons deal reduced damage to bosses unless specialized by props.
Summons lose uptime in dense obstacle layouts.
Summons should not fully inherit projectile multipliers without strict caps.

Milestone unlock plan:
Milestone 1: basic summon follower and respawn system.
Milestone 2: summon command key and target-priority AI.
Milestone 3: archetype split (Swarm, Familiar, Warden) with unique passives.
Milestone 4: a legendary summon prop that changes the run win condition.

Boss concept placeholder:
Boss: Anti-U

Rarity Policy
Use numeric rarity for fast tuning:
1 Common: very frequent in the shop, almost never used as a boss reward.
2 Uncommon: medium frequency.
3 Rare: low frequency early, then increases later.
4 Epic: very low chance in the shop; usually appears through bosses.

Shop rarity rule:
Higher rarity means lower shop probability.
Shop refresh growth can increase higher-rarity availability as level increases.

Rarity progression rule:
Lower rarities keep higher base weight.
Higher rarities keep lower base weight but higher growth per level.
