6. Core Paint System
Tiles can hold temporary "paint" that affects movement and combat. A tile¡¯s paint has:
Owner state: Neutral / Player Paint / Enemy Paint (enemy paint optional for later).
Intensity: 0-1, starts high when applied, then decays over time. Effects scale with intensity.
Sources of paint include:
Player movement (trails / footsteps).
Some attacks (projectiles, explosions, AoE splashes).
Boss skills (enemy ink zones).
Props that convert shield, HP, or kills into paint.
Player Paint baseline behavior:
While standing on Player Paint:
Apply a small move-speed bonus within the global speed cap.
Apply a small damage bonus against enemies standing on player-owned paint.
Optional extensions: minor HP or shield regen and faster special-meter gain.
Enemy Paint baseline behavior (future scope):
Apply slow and optional chip damage or debuffs (fog, blind, crit reduction), creating reclaim pressure.
Paint always decays over time so the battlefield remains dynamic.
New paint can overwrite existing paint under the overwrite rules below.

Core runtime rules:
Paint update tick: every 0.1s.
Default intensity decay: intensity -= 0.22 per second (clamp 0..1).
Tile ownership overwrite priority: latest timestamp wins.
Tile cleanup threshold: remove paint entry when intensity < 0.05.
Recommended hard cap: max 900 active paint tiles; if exceeded, evict oldest 10% by timestamp.

Suggested Player Paint formula:
move_speed_bonus = min(+12%, +12% * intensity)
damage_bonus_on_painted_targets = min(+10%, +10% * intensity)
optional_shield_regen = 0.0 / 0.2 / 0.4 shield per second (enabled by props only)

Suggested Enemy Paint formula:
player_slow = min(25%, 25% * intensity)
chip_damage = max_hp * 0.6% per second at full intensity
status_debuff_window = apply only if standing >= 0.8s continuously on enemy paint

