13. Runtime State Machine (Per Prop Trigger Type)
13.1. On-hit props (Bleed, DoT, Chill, Mark prep)
State flow:
IDLE -> HIT_DETECTED -> PROC_CHECK -> APPLY_EFFECT -> COOLDOWN/GCD -> IDLE
Rules:
Use a deterministic proc seed per hit event id to preserve replay consistency.
If multiple on-hit props trigger, process them in fixed prop-id order to avoid nondeterminism.

13.2. On-kill props (Shrapnel, Explosive chain, coin split)
State flow:
KILL_DETECTED -> SPAWN_PAYLOAD -> VALIDATE_CHAIN_DEPTH -> APPLY_CAPS -> COMPLETE
Rules:
Do not re-enter the same kill event more than once.
Track chain_origin_id to prevent infinite recursive effect loops.

13.3. On-damage-taken props (Mirror Shell, Retaliation Core, Guardian Charm)
State flow:
DAMAGE_PACKET -> SHIELD_STAGE -> HP_STAGE -> THRESHOLD_TRIGGERS -> BUFF_APPLY
Rules:
All reaction props must read post-mitigation damage values.
Require per-source throttles for rapid projectile-spam scenarios.

