30. Summoner Path Build Requirements (Detailed)
30.1. Role definition
The Summoner path should feel like force multiplication through unit composition, not passive background damage.
Player should make frequent tactical choices:
Positioning, summon timing, command focus target, and unit upgrade route.

30.2. Minimum viable summon roster
Frontline summon:
High aggro draw, low DPS, moderate durability.
Ranged summon:
Low durability, scaling sustained DPS.
Utility summon:
Applies slow/mark/debuff with lower direct damage.
Ultimate summon:
Timed high-impact unit with long cooldown or special resource.

30.3. Core stat framework
Summon cap (base + scaling)
Summon duration and respawn cadence
Summon damage scaling from player stats
AI response delay and retarget interval
Survivability lane:
HP/armor/resist parameters plus boss-damage modifier

30.4. Counterplay and balance controls
Global cap on total summon entities to protect FPS.
Diminishing returns on overlapping aura buffs.
Use boss anti-summon mechanics on select encounters (zone clear, fear pulse, target swap) so play remains interactive.
A Summoner run should still fail if the player ignores movement and defensive timing.

30.5. Shop-path readability for summoner cards
All summoner cards use green outline + summon icon + SUM label.
Tooltip first line format:
[SUMMONER] + short role tag (Spawner, Commander, Sustain, Sacrifice).
Card VFX should include a subtle pulsing edge to distinguish them from crit and economy cards.

